  "system": {
    "description": "<p><span >You learn 2 Monk Stances from the list below.</span></p><ul><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.885bXqRvBjj9VTxZ]{Bear Stance (Big Hits)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.rBUhXnddYVgeFt9r]{Bull Stance (Knockback)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.lJ7Eiar4oxTM3tZa]{Cobra Stance (Counter)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.1P85zZJWE3u2E87u]{Gazelle Stance (Nimble)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.sE5qC7YlF8rg89Me]{Mantis Stance (Grapple)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.UtB9E7iPXF7Nv70I]{Mongoose Stance (Multi)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.tLefke7qs8LHjBJH]{Scorpion Stance (Quick Strike)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.zT30vO0vD2zHZn3k]{Turtle Stance (Sturdy)}</p></li><li><p>@UUID[Compendium.dc20rpg.classes.Item.Ioc0SSJfi50h1J4j]{Wolf Stance (Hit & Run)}</p></li></ul><p><strong>Entering & Exiting:</strong> In Combat at the start of each of your turns you can freely enter or swap into one of your Monk Stances. You can also spend <strong>1 SP</strong> on your turn to swap to a different stance. You can end your Stance at any moment for free. You can only be in 1 Monk Stance at a time.</p>",
